column5: Hey Everyone!   Got down to the POOL yesterday with a new buddy who has never been.   - Temperatures were good (Compared to what we have been getting) - There was a fair bit of ice & slush - 1 out 3 successful casts - BRING a NET!   We ended up with (2) Browns. Lost (2) through the ice & slush Guy beside us caught nice Rainbow  It was a nice outing.   Minnow- Float Drifting  *no success (Roe, Pinks - chucking spoons & spinners)
edit: nevermind I should have read your post more carefully...  great job!
Great that you finally got down. Nice that you hooked into a few as well.
Nice looking fish. I am going to make the pool this year.Just like to get a few others to cut the cost, to go.
Nice fish. The Niagara is a nice place to fish in the winter, and the exercise is good too
did you lose the fish trying to get photos? You gotta be serious to fish in those conditions, in that location....I commend your effort!!!
Thanks for the insight Aaron, didn't know that
I could have sworn that your report used to say you caught one brown and one steelhead, and you even had a picture of the steelie???  Are my eyes decieving me or are you?
I think you mean this fish, I don't like it when people take pics of the fish I caught and then claim it was there's
Aha, so I'm not going crazy.  sorry to hear bongo, but some folks will do anything for a bit of glory.
What's the story with the pics Blair, Bongo?
he probably wants to look like an internet hero
Im hopeing he was misunderstood. Easy fellas.
I hope not 'cause that would just be some funny!
Sorry guys, this one is just going sour.
